Class DataColumnAddition

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.transform.column.ColumnWiseDataTableTransformation

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataTableTransformation, MutatingDataTableTransformation

    public class DataColumnAddition
extends ColumnWiseDataTableTransformation
implements MutatingDataTableTransformation
    The DataColumnAddition class is a mutating data table transformation which appends columns to the input table.

      • DataColumnAddition

        public DataColumnAddition()
        Constructor for an empty transformation. The transformation will do nothing until column additions are specified.

      • DataColumnAddition

        public DataColumnAddition(java.lang.String name,
                  DataType type,
                  Function1<DataRow,?> columnFunction)
        Convenience constructor initializing the transformation with a single column addition.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the column to add.
        type - The type of data held by the column to add.
        columnFunction - The function identifying the initial values of the new column. This function takes as its sole argument the data row of the input table, before the column has been added.

    • Method Detail

      • addColumn

        public void addColumn(java.lang.String name,
             DataType type,
             Function1<DataRow,?> columnFunction)
        Specify column to add to the data table. This column will be added after all of those specified before this one have been added (so the values of those additions should be available to this one).
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the column to add.
        type - The type of data held by the column to add.
        columnFunction - The function identifying the initial values of the new column. This function takes as its sole argument the data row of the input table, before the column has been added.
